CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
Children's Privacy
At MCookie.io, we are committed to protecting the privacy of our young users. We have developed our Children's Privacy Policy in compliance with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) in the United States and other applicable laws and regulations to ensure the safety and privacy of children using our platform.

Collection of Children's Personal Information

We collect limited personal information from children under the age of 13 (or the applicable age threshold in your country) only with verifiable parental consent. The personal information we collect may include the child's name, date of birth, and email address. We may also collect the parent's or guardian's name and email address for the purpose of obtaining verifiable parental consent.

Parental Consent

Before we collect, use, or disclose personal information from children, we will obtain verifiable parental consent. We will notify the parent or guardian about the types of information we collect and the purposes for which we use the information. Parents or guardians have the option to consent to the collection and use of their child's information without consenting to the disclosure of that information to third parties.

Parental Rights

Parents or guardians have the right to:

a. Review the personal information we have collected from their child; 
b. Request that we delete their child's personal information; 
c. Refuse further collection or use of their child's information; and 
d. Revoke their previously provided consent.

To exercise any of these rights, please contact us:

By email: info@mcookie.io By visiting our website: mcookie.io/contact

Data Retention

We retain personal information collected from children for only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected or as required by applicable laws and regulations. We will take reasonable measures to delete the information when it is no longer needed.

Security

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the personal information of children against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

Changes to Children's Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update or modify this Children's Privacy Policy at any time, in our sole discretion. If we make changes, we will post the updated Children's Privacy Policy on our website and update the "Last updated" date. Your continued use of our platform or services after any such changes constitutes your acceptance of the new Children's Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to any of these Children's Privacy Policy terms or any future changes, you must not use or access our platform or services.

